	(227,'external_updates-event-espresso','O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:9:\"lastCheck\";i:1359415512;s:14:\"checkedVersion\";s:10:\"3.1.29.1.P\";s:6:\"update\";O:19:\"PluginUpdateUtility\":7:{s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"5039\";s:4:\"slug\";s:14:\"event-espresso\";s:7:\"version\";s:10:\"3.1.29.1.P\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:34:\"http://eventespresso.com/features/\";s:12:\"download_url\";s:230:\"http://eventespresso.com?pu_request_plugin=event-espresso&pu_get_download=1&pue_active_version=3.1.29.1.P&site_domain=localhost%3A8888%2FPLS&pue_install_key=1307111810&pu_plugin_api=9ea20a5279a779c3a195921b61912d76&new_pue_check=1\";s:8:\"sections\";O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:11:\"description\";s:150:\"This premium plugin and event framework for WordPress allows you to turn your existing blog or website into a fully-featured event management website.\";s:12:\"installation\";s:437:\"<ol>\r\n<li>Upload the new version via your WordPress Plugins page or via FTP</li>\r\n<li>Deactivate the old version</li>\r\n<li>Activate the new version</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>If you have problems with the automatic update, see our <a href=\"http://eventespresso.com/wiki/installation/\">Installation instructions</a><br />\r\n</p><p><strong>*Note: We recommend making a backup of your WordPress database as you usually do before upgrading.</strong></p>\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:2526:\"6 December, 2012\r\n<strong id=\"3.1.29\">3.1.29.1</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Fixes</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>add to calendar button outputting part of the event description</li>\r\n	<li>iCal link breaks if there is a link in the event description</li>\r\n	<li>Missing argument for wp_kses() in email.php\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Attendee ID is displaying on the payment page</li>\r\n	<li>Error  on payment overview page</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Multi Event Registration: radio button answer values do not \"Copy\" to all forms</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n5 December, 2012\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Fixes</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>time slot limit feature counts incomplete registrations toward max registration limit</li>\r\n	<li>Fix the Multi Event Registration display</li>\r\n	<li>MER Ajax price display breaks when SSL is forced on registration page</li>\r\n	<li>Members: incorrect ticket price type label displayed in MER shopping cart</li>\r\n	<li>Undefined variable Errors in Event Editor</li>\r\n	<li>Undefined index Error on Attendee Reports admin page after clicking \"This Month\" filter</li>\r\n	<li>Undefined variable Errors in Event Editor after Fresh Install</li>\r\n	<li>full logging security fix</li>\r\n	<li>Percentage surcharge not calculated correctly using standard PayPal IPN</li>\r\n	<li>attendee exports push data to next column when multiple choice answers are selected</li>\r\n	<li>Undefined variable Error when updating from .27.1 to .28.3</li>\r\n	<li>Attendee records added prior to 3.1.28 do not allow payment updates via admin</li>\r\n	<li>question input strips all html</li>\r\n	<li>Missing argument 2 for wpdb::prepare() in WP 3.5</li>\r\n	<li>Authorize.net Line item 1 is invalid</li>\r\n	<li>Venue title not showing on address in registration page</li>\r\n	<li>Missing argument 2 for wpdb::prepare() Errors in the Event Editor with WP 3.5</li>\r\n	<li>First Data sending 0.00 amount</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><em>Updates</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Removed the \"Events expire on registration end date\" setting</li>\r\n	<li>Admin : limit the query for number of attendees or events on the admin screen</li>\r\n	<li>Link to REM from EE event edit screen is wrong</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong>New features</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>eway rapid 3.0 gateway</li>\r\n	<li>Add to Google/iCal/Outlook Calendar</li>\r\n	<li>event featured image thumbnail in event list</li>\r\n	<li>Add nice looking but generic \"Pay by Credit Card\" image for gateways</li>\r\n	<li>Make registration forms mobile browser compatible</li>\r\n	<li>BNP Mercanet - ATOS Worldwide gateway</li>\r\n	<li>Beanstream Gateway</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\";}s:14:\"upgrade_notice\";s:80:\"<p>This update is <strong>required</strong> if you upgrade WordPress to 3.5.</p>\";}}','yes'),
