	(230,'external_updates-espresso-members','O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:9:\"lastCheck\";i:1359415514;s:14:\"checkedVersion\";s:5:\"1.9.6\";s:6:\"update\";O:19:\"PluginUpdateUtility\":7:{s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"5670\";s:4:\"slug\";s:16:\"espresso-members\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"1.9.6\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:26:\"/product/espresso-members/\";s:12:\"download_url\";s:226:\"http://eventespresso.com?pu_request_plugin=espresso-members&pu_get_download=1&pue_active_version=1.9.6&site_domain=localhost%3A8888%2FPLS&pue_install_key=742123734&pu_plugin_api=9ea20a5279a779c3a195921b61912d76&new_pue_check=1\";s:8:\"sections\";O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:11:\"description\";s:354:\"The WP User Integration addon allows you to take full advantage of the WordPress user system. Give your users member discounts or access to member-only events with Event Espresso’s Member Integration add-on. Logged in users will have a My Events screen which allows them to keep track of events they’ve registered for or to cancel their registration.\";s:12:\"installation\";s:1006:\"This plugin/addon needs to be uploaded to the \"/wp-content/plugins/\" directory on your server or installed using the WordPress plugins installer.\r\n\r\nOnce the plugin/addon is installed and activated you will have a \"Member Settings\" tab in the left menu of your WordPress admin under the \"Event Manager\" tab. To make an event a \"Member Only\" event. Edit the event and choose Yes in the \"Is this a member only event?\" under the \"Attendees\" section of the event editor.\r\n\r\nMember Settings Page:\r\nThis page will allow you to do the following.\r\n	- Choose a Login page (if different from default WordPress login page) used for the link that will appear if a member is not logged in and trying to access a member only event.\r\n	- Choose a Member registration page (if different from default WordPress register page) used for the link that will appear if a member is not logged in and trying to access a member only event.\r\n	- Require login for all events? Allows you to make all of your events, member only events.\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:326:\"<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Fixes</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Undefined index Error after saving options on Manage Member Settings admin page</li>\r\n	<li>Missing argument 2 for wpdb::prepare() on Confirmation page with WP 3.5</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong>New features</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>front-end user profile edit page</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\";}s:14:\"upgrade_notice\";s:78:\"This update is <strong>required</strong> if you are updating WordPress to 3.5.\";}}','yes'),
