ore Easy WordPress Security: Change the WordPress MySQL database user password.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/tgMEixLJOHI/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:110:\"http://worpit.com/2012/12/more-easy-wordpress-security-change-wordpress-mysql-database-user-password/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 06 Dec 2012 22:35:53 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"WordPress Guides\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2973\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:155:\"Changing the WordPress Database user password is easier than ever, with Worpit. No more editing wp-config or phpMyAdmin. Just give the new password and go!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3752:\"<p></p><p><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" title=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>Worpit now has the ability to reset your WordPress MySQL database user password.</p>\n<p>Yes, it&#8217;s that time again: more WordPress security made easy with Worpit!</p>\n<p>This is not something you need to do often, but it&#8217;s one of those things that has 4 or 5 separate steps to it, and that makes automating the task a small joy.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2973\"></span></p>\n<h2>Why would you change the WordPress MySQL Database User Password?</h2>\n<p>You would do this basically for the same reason you rotate any passwords. Security maintenance.</p>\n<p>Using the same password long-term has inherent risks. Regularly updating the password does no harm.</p>\n<p>If at any time you suspect anyone has your WordPress database login credentials, simply changing your password will lock them out.</p>\n<p>The topic of recovering a compromised WordPress site is huge, and I&#8217;ll not go into it here.</p>\n<p>Suffice it to say, there are many things to be done during recovery, and changing the password is one option along the road.</p>\n<h2>What does changing the WordPress MySQL Database User Password involve?</h2>\n<p>There are 2 main steps involved here.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Change the password for the MySQL database user.</li>\n<li>Update the WordPress wp-config.php with the new MySQL password</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Neither of these are difficult, but can be a little time consuming if you have many sites you need to perform this on.</p>\n<p>This is where Worpit helps as it provides an interface to directly making these changes without you having to do any of the heavy lifting.</p>\n<h2>How to change the WordPress MySQL Password the easy way: Worpit</h2>\n<div id=\"attachment_2994\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 498px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/worpit-reset-wordpress-mysql-database-password1.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-2994 \" title=\"Worpit: Reset WordPress MySQL Database User Password\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/worpit-reset-wordpress-mysql-database-password1.png\" alt=\"Worpit: Reset WordPress MySQL Database User Password\" width=\"488\" height=\"152\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Easily reset WordPress Database Password using Worpit</p></div>\n<p>It&#8217;s easy to update your MySQL user password with Worpit. You simply supply the new password, confirm you&#8217;re ready to do it, and click the button.</p>\n<p>This feature may not work if you have 2 security settings in place, namely:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>PHP cannot write to your wp-config.php file, and/or</li>\n<li>PHP cannot use the exec to make system calls</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If your system doesn&#8217;t support it, it wont make the change and will leave your site intact. That said though, it&#8217;s always important to have a backup of your database and wp-config.php file.</p>\n<h2>Get the Worpit WordPress Advantage today</h2>\n<p>Managing all your WordPress websites is fun again with Worpit. You can perform many different WordPress management tasks to do with plugins, themes, security, and more.</p>\n<p>Best of all, you can perform them in bulk across all your sites.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s never been easier to manage all your WordPress sites &#8211; and it&#8217;s <a title=\"Manage Multiple WordPress Websites With Worpit!\" href=\"http://worpitapp.com/dashboard/signup\" target=\"_blank\">free to sign-up and get started</a>!</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/tgMEixLJOHI\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:106:\"http://worpit.com/2012/12/more-easy-wordpress-security-change-wordpress-mysql-database-user-password/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"http://worpit.com/2012/12/more-easy-wordpress-security-change-wordpress-mysql-database-user-password/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup: A few common pre-signup questions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/-WXPjVzav54/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-common-pre-signup-questions/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 29 Nov 2012 16:34:44 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WorpDrive\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2964\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"A few common questions answered about the WorpDrive WordPress Backup and Recovery service.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3615:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-2522\" title=\"WorpDrive: Automated WordPress Backup\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/WorpDrive-WordPress-Backup-Logo-200px.png\" alt=\"WorpDrive: Automated WordPress Backup\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />Yesterday we launched <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup and Recovery\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup</a> to the public, on our Worpit platform.</p>\n<p>So far so great!</p>\n<p>It turns out lots of people have been waiting for its release and the response we&#8217;ve received has been positive and a little overwhelming.</p>\n<p>Here are some of the most common questions we&#8217;ve had&#8230;</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2964\"></span></p>\n<h3 class=\"clear\">1. What is the space limit on WorpDrive for 1 site?</h3>\n<p>There is no space limit for WorpDrive.</p>\n<p>One WorpDrive license provides 1GB storage space. If you exceed this space, the system will automatically increment your WorpDrive licenses by 1, thereby adding an extra 1GB space.</p>\n<h3>2. Can I share my disk space between sites if one has more than 1GB and one has less.</h3>\n<p>Yes. The total disk quota in WorpDrive is shared. So if you have 3 WorpDrive licenses, you have a total of 3GB backup space that can be used by those 3 websites.</p>\n<h3>3. What technology does WorpDrive use? How does it work?</h3>\n<p>WorpDrive uses lots of different technology, and a lot of in-house custom-built software to run.  It doesn&#8217;t use <em>any WordPress code</em> to do what it does.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s fundamentally a combination of FTP and <a title=\"Subversion (SVN)\" href=\"http://subversion.apache.org/\" target=\"_blank\">SVN</a>.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive creates a replica of your website, and does a dump of your WordPress database. Then it adds all this to a new SVN repository.</p>\n<h3>4. How long does WorpDrive activation take?  It seems to take a long time&#8230;</h3>\n<p>This is expected. WorpDrive activation is dependent on 2 main factors:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>How big your site is. The bigger it is, the longer it will take to replicate and then add to the respository.</li>\n<li>Where your site is in the queue. We have a first-in-first-out activation queue as we don&#8217;t want to overload our infrastructure. Your site will be processed when it&#8217;s next up in the queue.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>5. How long would backups take if activation takes a long time?</h3>\n<p>Backups are only capturing the changes and should happen relatively very quickly.</p>\n<h3>6. Is Worpit included with WorpDrive, or the other way about?</h3>\n<p>No. Think of Worpit as the platform upon which you manage all your WordPress sites in one place.</p>\n<p>Then consider WorpDrive as the website backup component of your management tasks.</p>\n<p>At the moment, you must have Worpit to use WorpDrive&#8230; that will probably change in the future.</p>\n<p>Worpit licenses are completely independent of WorpDrive licenses.</p>\n<h2>Any more questions?</h2>\n<p>If you have any questions or suggestions, please feel free to contact us either directly from within Worpit itself, or <a title=\"Contact Worpit\" href=\"http://worpit.com/help-support/contact/\">on the website</a>.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re more than happy to get your feedback, and help you if you have any issues or want more information.</p>\n<p>If you want to try Worpit, you can <a title=\"Worpit App: Manage Multiple WordPress Websites\" href=\"https://worpitapp.com/dashboard/signup\" target=\"_blank\">sign-up today for free here</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/-WXPjVzav54\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-common-pre-signup-questions/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-common-pre-signup-questions/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup: Ultra-Reliable WordPress backup is available for all\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/HA4KkUBPEuE/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-ultra-reliable-wordpress-backup/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 28 Nov 2012 12:56:09 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WorpDrive\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2922\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:156:\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup is live and available for everyone. Finally, ultra-reliable WordPress Backup is within reach of all website owners big and small.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4919:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-2522\" title=\"WorpDrive: Ultra-Reliable WordPress Backup\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/WorpDrive-WordPress-Backup-Logo-200px.png\" alt=\"WorpDrive: Ultra-Reliable WordPress Backup\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />Today Worpit has released WorpDrive WordPress Backup.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive is an <em>all-new approach</em> to WordPress data protection and recovery.</p>\n<p>It is built to be highly reliable, cloud-based, and available to all website owners big and small.</p>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info clear\">WorpDrive is currently on promotion for a <strong>limited launch offer</strong>. All sites are £2.00 / €2,50 / US$3.00 with 1GB storage. The price you pay today is the price you always pay.</div>\n<h2>What is WorpDrive?</h2>\n<p>WorpDrive is super-charged WordPress Backup and Recovery.</p>\n<p>Some of the great features WorpDrive offers as standard &#8230;</p>\n<ol style=\"list-style-position: outside;\">\n<li>Never worry about backups again &#8211; it&#8217;s completely <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #1 – Complete Automation\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-1-complete-automation/\" target=\"_blank\">automatic WordPress Backup</a>.</li>\n<li>Security &#8211; all data is <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #2 – Ultimate WordPress Backup Security\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-2-ultimate-backup-security/\" target=\"_blank\">securely encrypted, and is WordPress-<strong>independent</strong></a>.</li>\n<li>You can test every backup &#8211; WorpDrive lets you <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #3 – Proof That Your Backup Actually Works\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-3-proof-your-backup-works/\" target=\"_blank\">test that your WordPress backup works</a>.</li>\n<li>You can <em><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #4 – Reveal The Mystery Inside Your Backups\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-4-reveal-mystery-inside-backups/\" target=\"_blank\">see inside your WordPress backups</a></em> &#8211; WorpDrive lets you see precisely the files that have changed and their contents.</li>\n<li><strong>Stress-Free WordPress Backups &#8211; <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #5 – No more stress, Reliable WordPress Backup\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-5-no-more-stress-reliable-wordpress-backup/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive just works</a>.</strong></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive Features and Benefits\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com/worpdrive-benefits/\" target=\"_blank\">more&#8230;</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p><span id=\"more-2922\"></span></p>\n<h2>How does WorpDrive work?</h2>\n<p>WorpDrive is far cleverer than traditional backup services that use clunky ZIPs and WordPress plugins.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive WordPress Backup only copies the changes that have happened on your site. It doesn&#8217;t copy everything, every time &#8211; that&#8217;s a waste.</p>\n<p>Using technology that professional software developers use, we have been able to build a system designed to work specifically with your WordPress website.</p>\n<p>And the result is a WordPress Backup system that is un-matched in speed, features, and reliability.</p>\n<h2>How can you get WorpDrive?</h2>\n<p>Easy!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Signup for your <a title=\"Manage Multiple WordPress websites with Worpit\" href=\"https://worpitapp.com/dashboard/welcome/?src=worpdrive-launch\" target=\"_blank\">free Worpit account here</a>.</li>\n<li>Add a website to your Worpit account</li>\n<li>Test it for <a title=\"Get WorpDrive WordPress Backup Compatible\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com/get-worpdrive-compatibility/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive compatibility</a></li>\n<li>Activate WorpDrive WordPress Backup</li>\n<li>Relax</li>\n<li>(If you need more, subscribe to more Worpit sites and then activate WorpDrive on them)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>WorpDrive is designed to be as simple, and as user-friendly as possible.</p>\n<p>You don&#8217;t even need to setup Amazon S3, or Dropbox, or any other storage provider. This is all handled for you.</p>\n<h2>What makes WorpDrive extra special? &#8211; the Worpit Advantage.</h2>\n<p>WorpDrive is built into Worpit &#8211; an all-in-one WordPress Management System.</p>\n<p>Worpit is custom built for you, to make your WordPress life easier.</p>\n<p>So now, not only can you manage the plugins, themes, security, and updates for your all your WordPress website in 1 place, you can manage their regular backup and recovery too.</p>\n<p>Worpit is free to start and you can <a title=\"Manage Multiple WordPress websites with Worpit\" href=\"https://worpitapp.com/dashboard/signup\" target=\"_blank\">sign-up here any time</a>. No credit cards, no billing information, just a free account.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/HA4KkUBPEuE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-ultra-reliable-wordpress-backup/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-ultra-reliable-wordpress-backup/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"Increased Worpit Security: Account PIN\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/oHMduAPM0Vc/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/increased-worpit-security-account-pin/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 26 Nov 2012 14:47:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"WordPress News and Updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2892\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:155:\"All sensitive Worpit features are protected by a second layer of security: Account PIN. It\'s easy to setup and easy to use. Here, we explain more about it.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4973:\"<p></p><p><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" title=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>At Worpit, our goal is to help you do more, in less time, with your WordPress sites.</p>\n<p>At the same time, <a title=\"Worpit Security: How does Worpit handle security of your WordPress site and your data?\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/07/worpit-security-how-worpit-handle-security-wordpress-data/\">security</a> is a <a title=\"Worpit Now Enforces Secure SSL\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/07/worpit-enforces-secure-ssl/\">top priority</a> <a title=\"How does Worpit handle security of client financial data?\" href=\"http://worpit.com/faq/how-does-worpit-handle-security-of-client-financial-transactions/\">for Worpit</a>.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re constantly improving our systems to ensure all data is secure and protected.</p>\n<p>And today we&#8217;ve released an update to protect you further: Account PINs.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2892\"></span></p>\n<h2>What is the Worpit Account PIN?</h2>\n<p>We know that typing in a password every time you want to do something can be a serious pain.</p>\n<p>Of course, you must always log into your Worpit account using your password, but we&#8217;ve now added the ability to create an account PIN.</p>\n<p>This PIN will protect certain Worpit features on your WordPress sites.</p>\n<p>For example, Worpit lets you log into all your WordPress sites with the click of a button.  We think this feature should have an extra layer of protection.</p>\n<p>If we were to protect it with your account password, we see 3 potential problems:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>you&#8217;re might decide to chose a less-secure account password that&#8217;s easier to remember, or</li>\n<li>you use a password manager to remember your password &#8211; if someone gets access to your browser or your manager, you&#8217;re in trouble, or</li>\n<li>typing in your password makes the service so user-<strong>unfriendly</strong> that you wont use it. And that would make us sad <img src=\'http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif\' alt=\':(\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </li>\n</ol>\n<p>This is why the Account PIN has been created &#8211; you can chose a PIN number of at least 4 digits and use this to access certain restricted features on your Worpit account.</p>\n<p>That way, there is no big password to remember, and all sensitive account features are protected by a <strong>second security layer</strong>.</p>\n<p>Win &#8211; Win!</p>\n<h2>How does the secure PIN feature work?</h2>\n<p>It&#8217;s easy.  If you haven&#8217;t set a PIN, you&#8217;ll just enter your account password where prompted to do so.</p>\n<p>To setup your PIN, go to your <a title=\"Worpit App Account Profile\" href=\"https://worpitapp.com/dashboard/profile\" target=\"_blank\">Account Profile in Worpit</a>, then select the &#8216;Password and PIN&#8217; tab.</p>\n<p>Enter your existing account password (the PIN cannot be set without this) in the first box, and supply your PIN (as seen in the screen-shot below).</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2894\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-password-and-pin.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2894 \" title=\"Worpit Password and PIN\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-password-and-pin-300x182.png\" alt=\"Worpit Password and PIN\" width=\"300\" height=\"182\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Worpit Password and PIN</p></div>\n<p>Once this PIN has been set, each time you try to access a Worpit feature that we feel is sensitive enough to require a PIN, you will be prompted to enter it:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2897\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-enter-password-pin-dialog.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2897\" title=\"Worpit: Enter Password or PIN dialog\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-enter-password-pin-dialog-300x134.png\" alt=\"Worpit: Enter Password or PIN dialog\" width=\"300\" height=\"134\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Worpit: Enter Password or PIN prompt</p></div>\n<p>We feel this greatly enhances and complements Worpit&#8217;s growing list of security features and protections.</p>\n<p>There are more planned, but we trust that our efforts so far indicate how much importance we place on your account data and its security.</p>\n<h2>Get the Worpit Advantage Today</h2>\n<p>Worpit lets you manage your plugins, themes, and security (and much more) across all your WordPress websites from one convenient, secure, dashboard.</p>\n<p>And it’s free to signup. No commitments, no credit cards.</p>\n<p>Just good WordPress management.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/oHMduAPM0Vc\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/increased-worpit-security-account-pin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/increased-worpit-security-account-pin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #5 – No more stress, Reliable WordPress Backup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/fGmiygbcXSw/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:114:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-5-no-more-stress-reliable-wordpress-backup/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 25 Nov 2012 13:16:57 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WorpDrive\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2833\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:150:\"WorpDrive offers you no-more-stress WordPress Backup and Recovery system. It takes control of your daily backups, so you don\'t have to worry any more.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6454:\"<p></p><div id=\"attachment_2861\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"width: 235px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/stress-free-wordpress-backup.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-2861 \" title=\"WorpDrive is stress-free WordPress Backup\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/stress-free-wordpress-backup-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"WorpDrive is stress-free WordPress Backup\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">WorpDrive is stress-free WordPress Backup</p></div>\n<p>Can you imagine the feeling of knowing all your WordPress websites are protected with a reliable WordPress backup service?</p>\n<p>Take a moment and think of all those frustrating little things you&#8217;d never have to do again (for every site!).</p>\n<p>How is WorpDrive different?</p>\n<p>WorpDrive is <strong>reliable</strong>.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2833\"></span></p>\n<h2 class=\"clear\">WorpDrive is different: it&#8217;s <em>reliable </em>WordPress Backup</h2>\n<p>Have you ever bought a backup service and it doesn&#8217;t work on your web hosting?</p>\n<p>Snap.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve all been there.</p>\n<p>Do you&#8230;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>get &#8220;PHP FATAL out of memory errors&#8221; with your backup plugin?</li>\n<li>have problems copying to Dropbox / S3 / &lt;<em>fill in your storage provider here</em>&gt; ?</li>\n<li>use lots of space on your server storing zip files of old backups?</li>\n<li>contact the author of the plugin explaining how your backup doesn&#8217;t work?</li>\n<li>search Google and support forums looking for people with the same problems as you?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You&#8217;re not alone.</p>\n<p>This is considered &#8220;normal&#8221; for WordPress backups.</p>\n<p>We decided to take a bold new approach to backing up your websites, something that was seemingly never thought of before:</p>\n<blockquote><p><strong>we wanted to remove all stress and frustration from WordPress backups for good</strong>.</p></blockquote>\n<p>We have built WorpDrive to be super-reliable WordPress backup. This has taken a lot of hard work, but we&#8217;ve finally made it.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive has a few special requirements that you must have on your web hosting before it will work.</p>\n<p>But the cool thing about WorpDrive, is that we wont let you activate it unless your website meets these requirements, and passes the compatibility tests with flying colours.</p>\n<p>Why?</p>\n<p>Because we know how frustrating it is to buy a backup product and discover you have nothing but problems with it.</p>\n<p>Sure, the problems might be because of your web hosting, or your WordPress configuration, or your PHP setup&#8230; doesn&#8217;t matter, it&#8217;s still frustrating.</p>\n<p>If your website passes the compatibility tests, it&#8217;ll run WorpDrive without any issues. You can then be confident that your sites are backed-up and <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #3 – Proof That Your Backup Actually Works\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-3-proof-your-backup-works/\">ready to be recovered the moment</a> you need it.</p>\n<h2>What makes WorpDrive such a reliable WordPress Backup?</h2>\n<p>Your WordPress site is basically a software program.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s constantly changing because you update plugins, themes and WordPress.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive backup system uses technology that software development companies use to manage their software.</p>\n<p>And why not? Why shouldn&#8217;t you take advantage of the same tools that developers use, to keep your WordPress site protected?</p>\n<p>WorpDrive has gone through many development phases before we deemed it good enough to be ready for you.</p>\n<p>We didn&#8217;t rush it out, trying to make quick money off sales.</p>\n<p>We tested, tested, and tested some more. Our beta testers can testify to this (thank you beta testers!).</p>\n<h2>Are your websites ready for reliable WordPress Backups?</h2>\n<p>If you <a title=\"Worpit App: Manage Multiple WordPress Websites\" href=\"http://worpitapp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">sign-up to Worpit today</a> (for free) you can start testing your websites to see if they&#8217;re ready.</p>\n<p>If you discover they&#8217;re not ready for WorpDrive, we&#8217;ll tell you what the problem is and you can ask your web host to help you fix the issues.</p>\n<p>The requirements aren&#8217;t crazy, and most quality web hosting companies will support WorpDrive. We&#8217;ll soon have a list of recommended web hosts to help you find compatible web hosting.</p>\n<h2>Why is WorpDrive not free?</h2>\n<p>Some people contact us expecting WorpDrive to be a part of Worpit and wonder why the backup system isn&#8217;t free.</p>\n<p>If you believe you can find a backup system that is free or even costs the same as WorpDrive and has all the features listed below, we&#8217;d like to know about it:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #1 – Complete Automation\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-1-complete-automation/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup is completely automatic</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #2 – Ultimate WordPress Backup Security\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-2-ultimate-backup-security/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup is secure</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #3 – Proof That Your Backup Actually Works\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-3-proof-your-backup-works/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup gives you proof that every backup works</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #4 – Reveal The Mystery Inside Your Backups\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-4-reveal-mystery-inside-backups/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup lets you see inside every backup</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup and Recovery Features\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com/worpdrive-benefits/\" target=\"_blank\">Many more features</a>&#8230;</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Get the Worpit Advantage Today!</h2>\n<p>Worpit lets you manage your plugins, themes, and security (and much more) across all your WordPress websites from one convenient, secure, dashboard.</p>\n<p>And it’s free to signup. No commitments, no credit cards.</p>\n<p>Just good WordPress management.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/fGmiygbcXSw\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:110:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-5-no-more-stress-reliable-wordpress-backup/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-5-no-more-stress-reliable-wordpress-backup/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"Secure WordPress Login and Admin Dashboard with SSL (HTTPS)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/TuHLnhBUov0/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/secure-wordpress-login-admin-dashboard-ssl-https/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 21 Nov 2012 11:27:44 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"WordPress Guides\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2763\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:155:\"Force SSL Admin and Force SSL Login are easy WordPress security features to set. All you need is an SSL certificate on your site and to follow this how-to.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7954:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" title=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />One of Worpit&#8217;s goals is to help you make all your WordPress websites more secure.</p>\n<p>Implementing good security principles isn&#8217;t difficult, but it&#8217;ll take you a long time to do on each site.</p>\n<p>So far we&#8217;ve shown you that Worpit can help keep your websites more secure by:</p>\n<ol style=\"clear: both;\">\n<li>regularly <a title=\"More WordPress Security: WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-wordpress-authentication-keys-salts/\">resetting the WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts</a>.</li>\n<li><a title=\"Changing the WordPress Database Table Prefix, Security through Obscurity\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/changing-wordpress-database-table-prefix-security-obscurity/\">renaming your WordPress database table prefix</a> to something other than the default.</li>\n<li><a title=\"More WordPress Security: Disallow File Edit Setting In WordPress\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-disallow-file-edit-setting-wordpress/\">disabling the ability to edit files</a> from within the WordPress dashboard.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>These are serious security advantages that reduce your surface area to attack.</p>\n<p>Worpit lets you put these protections in place with just a click of a button.</p>\n<p>WordPress has another useful option to sure-up your websites: SSL / HTTPS.</p>\n<p>By the end of this article you&#8217;ll understand all you need to know about enabling SSL or HTTPS on your WordPress admin, and of course how to do it.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2763\"></span></p>\n<h2>What&#8217;s the 1st thing you need to know about WordPress Admin and SSL?</h2>\n<p>The basic requirement for secure SSL logins to WordPress, and a secure SSL-based admin area, is the <em>presence of an SSL certificate</em>.</p>\n<p>If your website doesn&#8217;t have this, it&#8217;s not going to work.</p>\n<p>But all is not lost.. it is possible to use your web hosting control panel, or to ask your web host if you&#8217;re unsure how this is done, to create a &#8220;self-signed&#8221; SSL certificate.</p>\n<p>The self-signed certificate is only for website admin and not for any other purpose &#8211; if you enable SSL on your whole WordPress site you&#8217;re going to have a few issues with your visitors.</p>\n<p>Enabling SSL on a website is a much bigger topic than can be covered in this article, but I&#8217;ll assume that if you read on, you have a valid SSL certificate installed, whether certified/signed by a root certificate authority, or just self-signed.</p>\n<h2>WordPress Security Option 1: Force <em>Login</em> Over SSL</h2>\n<p>With this option enabled, the WordPress login is always <strong>forced</strong> over SSL.  That means the URL for submitting the login form will begin with <code>HTTPS://</code></p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t have an SSL certificate installed on your site (as mentioned earlier) you&#8217;ll face login problems so only do this if you&#8217;ve sorted this part out first.</p>\n<p>Since WordPress normally login runs over unsecured HTTP:// connections, usernames and passwords are sent as clear text and easily readable by someone who is looking closely at the traffic.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2823\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/force-ssl-login-form-source-wordpress.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2823\" title=\"Force SSL Login Form for WordPress\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/force-ssl-login-form-source-wordpress-300x30.png\" alt=\"Force SSL Login Form for WordPress\" width=\"300\" height=\"30\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Force SSL Login Form for WordPress</p></div>\n<p>With this option enabled, the problem of snooping is averted and you have a secure channel for submitting WordPress login information.</p>\n<p>After this is enabled, you&#8217;ll know it&#8217;s working when you look at the source of your login form page (see image).</p>\n<h2>WordPress Security Option 2: Force <em>Admin</em> Over SSL</h2>\n<p>When this option is enabled, it <strong>forces</strong> the whole of the WordPress Admin area (including logins and registrations) to be served with SSL &#8211; i.e. over HTTPS.</p>\n<p>This is the most ideal solution in terms of a secure connection, but again, you&#8217;ll need to have an SSL certificate installed for that site.</p>\n<h2>How to enable the FORCE_SSL security options on your WordPress sites &#8211; the easy way</h2>\n<div id=\"attachment_2765\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 357px\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2765 \" title=\"Force SSL Admin / Login for WordPress\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/force-ssl-admin-login-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Force SSL Admin / Login for WordPress\" width=\"347\" height=\"71\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Force SSL Admin / Login for WordPress</p></div>\n<p>As you probably know by now, Worpit is by far the easiest way to manage many of your WordPress security options.</p>\n<p>All you do is flick the switch, and Worpit will go off and make the necessary changes for you on each of your sites.</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t have a Worpit account, or you don&#8217;t want to sign-up for the free one (that includes these security tools as standard), then you can follow the how-to guide below.</p>\n<h2>How to enable the FORCE_SSL options within WordPress &#8211; the hard way</h2>\n<p>When you use Worpit to set this setting, you can turn it on and off quickly.</p>\n<p>This is useful if 99% of the time you don&#8217;t use the editor, but sometimes you want to just quickly make an edit. Worpit can let you turn off the setting, and then re-enable it as soon as you&#8217;re done.</p>\n<p>But, if you want to do it manually, it&#8217;s easy. Here&#8217;s how:</p>\n<h4>1. Make a backup of your wp-config.php file.</h4>\n<p>If you&#8217;re using a <a title=\"WordPress Backup and Recovery\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress backup system like WorpDrive</a>, just fire off a backup, wait until it&#8217;s completed and continue on.</p>\n<h4>2. Open up your wp-config.php file for editing.</h4>\n<p>Download the <code>wp-config.php</code> from your website and open it up in your favourite text editor</p>\n<h4>3. Find the setting FORCE_SSL_LOGIN in your wp-config.php and change it to true</h4>\n<p>By default, this setting is not specified in the WordPress wp-config.php file. If you&#8217;ve never set this before, it wont be there, and you&#8217;ll have to add it yourself.</p>\n<p>But you need to be careful where you add new configuration settings &#8211; you cannot add them to the end of the file.</p>\n<p>A good place to do it is after the line that sets <code>WP_DEBUG</code>.</p>\n<p>To enable this security setting, add the following line to your wp-config.php:</p>\n<pre>define( \'FORCE_SSL_LOGIN\', true );</pre>\n<h4>4. Repeat step 3 but for FORCE_SSL_ADMIN</h4>\n<p>Simply do what you did for step 3, but use this line:</p>\n<pre>define( \'FORCE_SSL_ADMIN\', true );</pre>\n<h4>5. Replace your wp-config.php</h4>\n<p>Save your <code>wp-config.php</code> file with the changes, and upload it back to your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;re done!</p>\n<h2>Get the Worpit Advantage Today &#8211; Free</h2>\n<p>This setting is also not a difficult security tasks, but made much easier when using Worpit if you have many websites to manage and maintain.</p>\n<p>Worpit lets you manage your plugins, themes, and security (and much more) across all your WordPress websites from one convenient, secure, dashboard.</p>\n<p>And it’s free to signup. No commitments, no credit cards.</p>\n<p>Just good WordPress management.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/TuHLnhBUov0\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/secure-wordpress-login-admin-dashboard-ssl-https/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/secure-wordpress-login-admin-dashboard-ssl-https/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"Lesson: Never be afraid to change your web host when they’re not performing as they should\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/LVPY-nBUxDc/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/lesson-never-be-afraid-change-web-host-when-performing-bad/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 20 Nov 2012 19:47:24 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2780\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:144:\"Who you host your WordPress sites with makes all the difference. Never be afraid to switch to something better. Here is a perfect example why...\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Paul G.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5308:\"<p></p><p>A couple of days ago Worpit received a tweet about our website being down.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/tweet-worpit-site-down.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2781 aligncenter\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\" title=\"Tweet: Worpit Website Down\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/tweet-worpit-site-down.png\" alt=\"Tweet: Worpit Website Down\" width=\"535\" height=\"110\" /></a></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s not something you want to wake up to in the morning.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re a small start-up business like us, you need all the up-time you can get.</p>\n<p>So I set to work to see if I could pin-point the problem and try to fix it.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2780\"></span></p>\n<h2>Web hosting problems are usually because of your web host</h2>\n<p>We take great care when we update our websites, and I hadn&#8217;t updated any of the Worpit site in the past 24-48hrs so I suspected it wasn&#8217;t a site coding issue.</p>\n<p>It was either down to 1 of 2 things.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cloudflare.com\" target=\"_blank\">Cloudflare</a>, or</li>\n<li>our web host &#8211; <a title=\"VPS.net cloud hosting\" href=\"http://bit.ly/MZWsZ0\" target=\"_blank\">VPS.net</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>We use <a title=\"CloudFlare – Boost your WordPress site security and performance in 10 minutes\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/08/cloudflare-boost-wordpress-security-performance/\" target=\"_blank\">cloudflare to help secure and improve our websites&#8217; performance</a>. It normally works excellent, but sometimes it takes a hit and our sites go a bit funky. Much less so now it has to be said.</p>\n<p>Turned out Cloudflare didn&#8217;t have any outages that would have affected our site around the time this tweet was posted so I ruled them out pretty quick.</p>\n<p>I then checked the error logs and it turned out that on several occasions the:</p>\n<pre>MySQL server has gone away</pre>\n<p>error was appearing in the logs much too often.</p>\n<p>This basically meant that the MySQL server for worpit.com was basically timing out &#8211; a connection was opened, and a request was made but no response from the MySQL process.</p>\n<p>We made the decision from the beginning to use a dedicated cloud hosting service from VPS.net for the Worpit.com website. In this way it would never be affected by issues that could affect the worpitapp.com service.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve had a few quirks with the hosting, but nothing crazy. On the whole it&#8217;s performed well enough.</p>\n<h2><em>Only that which is measured can be improved</em> &#8211; especially true of server  up-time and response time</h2>\n<p>I decided to start monitoring the Worpit site over a couple of days to see how it was doing.</p>\n<p>The tool I used to do this was <a title=\"Pingdom website monitoring\" href=\"http://www.pingdom.com\" target=\"_blank\">Pingdom.com</a>.</p>\n<p>This horrific result was this:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2795\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 238px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/pingdom-uptime-report-worpitcom.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2795\" title=\"Pingdom Uptime Report: Worpit.com\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/pingdom-uptime-report-worpitcom-228x300.png\" alt=\"Pingdom Uptime Report: Worpit.com\" width=\"228\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Pingdom Uptime Report: Worpit.com</p></div>\n<p>Clearly this doesn&#8217;t inspire confidence.</p>\n<p>I decided not to wait for the 24~48hrs I had initially planned, and set about moving the website to alternative hosting.</p>\n<p>Within an hour I had moved both worpit.com and worpdrive.com to one of our <a title=\"VPS Hosting with TMZ\" href=\"http://bit.ly/XxU7M3\" target=\"_blank\">servers hosted with TMZVPS.com</a>.</p>\n<p>Since the move, worpit.com has been offline once, and we got a great boost in server response time which increased on average by a factor of around 10x (see image below).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/pingdom-response-time-chart-worpitcom.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2797 aligncenter\" title=\"Pingdom Response Time Chart: Worpit.com\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/pingdom-response-time-chart-worpitcom-300x203.png\" alt=\"Pingdom Response Time Chart: Worpit.com\" width=\"300\" height=\"203\" /></a></p>\n<h2>Who you host your sites with makes all the difference</h2>\n<p>Don&#8217;t think that because you&#8217;re hosting with a big name, and they come highly recommend you should stick with them even when their performance is crappy.</p>\n<p>Who you host with is entirely up to you and it doesn&#8217;t matter who recommended them to you.</p>\n<p>Yes, it can be a pain to move your web hosting to another provider, but with the right setup from the start, and the right tools, it&#8217;s easy.</p>\n<p>Worpit will soon be releasing WordPress cloning and site migration tools so stay tuned.</p>\n<p>If you want to hear of new features as they&#8217;re released, sign-up for your free Worpit account.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Manage Multiple WordPress Websites with Worpit\" href=\"http://worpitapp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Get the Worpit Advantage</a> today!</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/LVPY-nBUxDc\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/lesson-never-be-afraid-change-web-host-when-performing-bad/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/lesson-never-be-afraid-change-web-host-when-performing-bad/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"More WordPress Security: Disallow File Edit Setting In WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/FMyYDEzPIRM/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-disallow-file-edit-setting-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 19 Nov 2012 10:17:40 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"WordPress Guides\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2747\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:148:\"Disallow File Edit is a great WordPress security setting that is easy - we show you exactly how. With Worpit, you have access to many more settings.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Paul G.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6177:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" title=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />In our last 2 articles on WordPress security, we&#8217;ve shown you how you can <a title=\"Changing the WordPress Database Table Prefix, Security through Obscurity\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/changing-wordpress-database-table-prefix-security-obscurity/\">quickly and easily take steps</a> to <a title=\"More WordPress Security: WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-wordpress-authentication-keys-salts/\">improve your WordPress security</a>.</p>\n<p>Here, I&#8217;m going to tell you of a WordPress configuration setting that will prevent editing any files from within your WordPress admin area, by users with unauthorized access.</p>\n<p>This is a simple WordPress configuration setting and is easy to implement.</p>\n<p>By the end of this article you will know what this setting is, why you would use it, and how to set it.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2747\"></span></p>\n<h2><em>Dissallow File Editing</em> setting within the WordPress admin dashboard</h2>\n<p>WordPress, by default, allows you the ability edit theme and plugin files directly from within the WordPress control panel.</p>\n<p>Useful, but potentially high risk.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s say that somehow, someone has gained admin privileges into your WordPress administration. If they want to add code to your WordPress site, all they need to do is jump onto the file editors and add any code they wish.</p>\n<p>This means they don&#8217;t FTP access or anything like that, as WordPress provides them all the access they need to edit files.</p>\n<p>If you never change files directly on your WordPress site, there&#8217;s absolutely no need to have this feature available to you or  your administrators.</p>\n<h2>How to disallow file editing within WordPress &#8211; the easy way</h2>\n<p>In Worpit, we&#8217;ve provided an interface to configuring many WordPress security settings across all your websites.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2751\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"width: 421px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/disallow_file_editing_wordpress_worpit.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2751 \" title=\"Disallow File Edit in WordPress using Worpit\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/disallow_file_editing_wordpress_worpit.png\" alt=\"Disallow File Edit in WordPress using Worpit\" width=\"411\" height=\"32\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Disallow File Edit in WordPress using Worpit</p></div>\n<p>This is just one of them.</p>\n<p>To disable file editing from within WordPress, simply browse to the &#8216;Security&#8217; tab for your site, and click the toggle switch to turn it on and off. Within a few moments, Worpit will configure this setting for you on your website.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s very easy, and you don&#8217;t need to worry about editing your wp-config.php file, FTP, uploading etc. It&#8217;s all done automatically for you.</p>\n<p>You will know that the setting has worked if you log into your WordPress site and you can no longer open the WordPress file editor.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2754\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 328px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/disallow_file_edit_no-wordpress-editor-menu.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2754\" title=\"Disallow File Edit - No WordPress Editor Menu Item\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/disallow_file_edit_no-wordpress-editor-menu.png\" alt=\"Disallow File Edit - No WordPress Editor Menu Item\" width=\"318\" height=\"170\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Disallow File Edit &#8211; No WordPress Editor Menu Item</p></div>\n<h2>How to disallow file editing within WordPress &#8211; the hard way</h2>\n<p>When you use Worpit to set this setting, you can turn it on and off quickly.</p>\n<p>This is useful if 99% of the time you don&#8217;t use the editor, but sometimes you want to just quickly make an edit. Worpit can let you turn off the setting, and then re-enable it as soon as you&#8217;re done.</p>\n<p>But, if you want to do it manually, it&#8217;s easy. Here&#8217;s how:</p>\n<h4>1. Make a backup of your wp-config.php file.</h4>\n<p>If you&#8217;re using a <a title=\"WordPress Backup and Recovery\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress backup system like WorpDrive</a>, just fire off a backup, wait until it&#8217;s completed and continue on.</p>\n<h4>2. Open up your wp-config.php file for editing.</h4>\n<p>Download your <code>wp-config.php</code> from your website and open it up in your favourite text editor</p>\n<h4>3. Find the setting DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT in your wp-config.php and change it to true</h4>\n<p>By default, this setting is not specified in the WordPress wp-config.php file. If you&#8217;ve never set this before, it wont be there, and you&#8217;ll have to add it yourself.</p>\n<p>But you need to be careful where you add new configuration settings &#8211; you cannot add them to the end of the file.</p>\n<p>A good place to do it is to look for <code>WP_DEBUG</code> and add it immediately after this line.</p>\n<p>To enable this security setting, add the following line to your wp-config.php:</p>\n<pre>define( \'DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT\', true );</pre>\n<h4>4. Replace your wp-config.php</h4>\n<p>Save your <code>wp-config.php</code> file with the new line added, and upload it back to your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll know it&#8217;s worked as outlined in the previous section.</p>\n<h2>Get the Worpit Advantage Today &#8211; Free</h2>\n<p>This setting is also not a difficult security tasks, but made much easier when using Worpit if you have many websites to manage and maintain.</p>\n<p>Worpit lets you manage your plugins, themes, and security (and much more) across all your WordPress websites from one convenient, secure, dashboard.</p>\n<p>And it’s free to signup. No commitments, no credit cards.</p>\n<p>Just good WordPress management.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/FMyYDEzPIRM\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-disallow-file-edit-setting-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-disallow-file-edit-setting-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"More WordPress Security: WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/45pCf5ArL-k/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-wordpress-authentication-keys-salts/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 17 Nov 2012 11:08:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"WordPress Guides\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2712\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:152:\"Resetting WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts is easy with Worpit and takes seconds to do. If you don\'t use Worpit I show you how to do it manually.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Paul G.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5223:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" title=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />Ever wondered how your WordPress site knows it&#8217;s <em>you</em> that&#8217;s logged in as admin and not someone else?</p>\n<p>WordPress doesn&#8217;t use sessions, but rather stores this information in a cookie (in your browser).</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re logged into a WordPress site, your cookie will identify you to it.</p>\n<p>To protect the information stored in your WordPress cookies, WordPress uses authentication keys and salts to encrypt it and reduce chances of your account being compromised.</p>\n<p>With enough time, information, and intelligence, most all encryption can be cracked eventually, so it&#8217;s a good idea to regularly update your WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts.</p>\n<p>By the end of this article you will know a bit more about what WordPress Authenticaion keys and salts are, and how you can change them easily.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2712\"></span></p>\n<h2>What are the WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts?</h2>\n<p>As already outlined, the WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts help protect your website from intrusion by encrypting the information that identifies you with the site.</p>\n<p>This information stored in your cookies is encrypted using the WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts that are defined in your <code>wp-config.php</code> file.</p>\n<p>It is recommended that you update these keys regularly and especially if you suspect that someone has gained unintentional access to the site.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s quite easy to do too.</p>\n<p>Remember: <em>When you update your keys and salts, all existing login sessions on the site will be terminated &#8211; that is to say, everyone will need to login again</em>.</p>\n<h2>How to update the WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts &#8211; the <em>easy way</em></h2>\n<p>Worpit has a growing collection of security tools designed to make protecting your WordPress sites easier to do.</p>\n<p>Worpit&#8217;s strength lies in its ability to run actions across all your websites in bulk, and resetting WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts is just one of them.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2714\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 295px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-feature-wordpress-authentication-keys-and-salts.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2714 \" title=\"Worpit Feature: WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-feature-wordpress-authentication-keys-and-salts.png\" alt=\"Worpit Feature: WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts\" width=\"285\" height=\"127\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Worpit Feature: WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts</p></div>\n<p>Resetting your keys and salts on any site is as easy as clicking a button (see image), and you even have the option to select all or some of your sites at once and run the reset tool.</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t have a free Worpit account you can of course do this manually, and its one of the easier security tasks to perform.</p>\n<p>But, you&#8217;ll want to do this regularly, which is where Worpit shines, as it removes the manual work altogether.</p>\n<p>So head on over to your free <a title=\"Worpit App: manage multiple WordPress websites.\" href=\"http://worpitapp.com\" target=\"_blank\">Worpit account and give it a go</a>!</p>\n<h2>How to update the WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts &#8211; the <em>hard way</em></h2>\n<p>There are 3 steps to resetting the keys and salts&#8230;</p>\n<h4>1. Backup your WordPress database and wp-config.php file</h4>\n<p>If you&#8217;re running <a title=\"WordPress Backup and Recovery\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com\">WorpDrive</a> on your WordPress site, simply run a quick backup, wait until it&#8217;s complete and continue on.</p>\n<h4>2. Get new authentication keys and salts</h4>\n<p>Open up the following link: <a title=\"WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts\" href=\"https://api.wordpress.org/secret-key/1.1/salt\" target=\"_blank\">https://api.wordpress.org/secret-key/1.1/salt</a></p>\n<p>and copy all the text in this page.</p>\n<h4>3. Edit your wp-config.php with the copied text from part (2)</h4>\n<p>Edit your <code>wp-config.php</code> file as you normally do and locate the section that has the text similar to that copied in part 2.</p>\n<p>Replace all 6 lines in the file with all six lines copied from part (2). Save and replace your wp-config.php file with the new contents.</p>\n<p>And you&#8217;re done!</p>\n<h2>Get the Worpit Advantage Today!</h2>\n<p>Certainly this is not one of the more difficult security related tasks, but made much easier when using Worpit if you have many websites to manage and maintain.</p>\n<p>Worpit lets you manage your plugins, themes, and security (and much more) across all your WordPress websites from <strong>one convenient, secure, dashboard</strong>.</p>\n<p>And it&#8217;s free to signup. No commitments, no credit cards.</p>\n<p>Just good WordPress management.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/45pCf5ArL-k\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-wordpress-authentication-keys-salts/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-wordpress-authentication-keys-salts/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"Changing the WordPress Database Table Prefix, Security through Obscurity\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/jSGXYghBNCE/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/changing-wordpress-database-table-prefix-security-obscurity/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 15 Nov 2012 20:21:06 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"WordPress Guides\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2678\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:139:\"Changing the WordPress Database Table Prefix is easy with Worpit and takes seconds. Or you can do it the long way, we show you exactly how.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Paul G.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8106:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" title=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />WordPress Security is a hot topic, and rightly so.</p>\n<p>If there are more than 70 millions WordPress sites, and your site is one of them, you better believe you&#8217;re a target.</p>\n<p>Most hacking attempts are attempted off the back of scans that are fired off across the web looking for sites with known vulnerabilities.</p>\n<p>If your site responds with a &#8220;Yes, I have that vulnerability&#8221;, you&#8217;re probably going to get picked apart.</p>\n<p>So how can we prevent this?</p>\n<p>By end of this series of articles on security, you&#8217;re going know all the easiest and most effective ways to minimize your surface area to attack.</p>\n<p>In the 1st article in this series, I&#8217;ll explain the <em>WordPress Database Table Prefix</em>, what it is, and how you can easily change it.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2678\"></span></p>\n<h2>What is the WordPress Database Table Prefix?</h2>\n<p>The WordPress database table prefix is simply a string of letters and numbers that are used when assigning names to the tables of the WordPress database.</p>\n<p>The default prefix is: <code>wp_</code></p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2682\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/wordpress-database-prefix-image.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2682  \" title=\"WordPress Database Table Prefix\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/wordpress-database-prefix-image-300x184.png\" alt=\"WordPress Database Table Prefix\" width=\"300\" height=\"184\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">WordPress Database Table Prefix example</p></div>\n<p>This means, if my WordPress site has the prefix &#8220;wp_&#8221;, all the tables in my database will begin with these 3 letters. (See the image)</p>\n<p>What has this got to do with security?</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s say there&#8217;s a vulnerability in a plugin, or even in WordPress itself that somehow allows for the execution of code/MySQL on your WordPress database, for example.</p>\n<p>As a hacker, I&#8217;m going to assume your database tables all begin with &#8220;wp_&#8221; and design any exploits accordingly. Chances are high that I&#8217;ll be right and I&#8217;ll get lucky.</p>\n<h2>Can the WordPress Database Prefix be changed?</h2>\n<p>Absolutely it can.</p>\n<p>But it&#8217;s quite a manual job.</p>\n<p>There are many reports of how it can be done, but experience has taught us that many how to guides out there are actually incomplete.</p>\n<p>Your site needs to know what your WordPress database table prefix is before it can load the site. And in order to tell it, the prefix is stored within your <code>wp-config.php</code> file.</p>\n<p>You can see it for yourself. Open up your wp-config.php file and look for the line that starts with: <code>$table_prefix</code></p>\n<p>That will tell you your prefix.</p>\n<p>Warning: don&#8217;t change your prefix yet!</p>\n<p>If you change your prefix in this file, and hope that the problem is solved, you&#8217;re wrong. There is much more to do.</p>\n<h2>How to rename the WordPress Database Prefix &#8211; the <em>easy way</em></h2>\n<p>The easiest way to do this is <strong>automatically</strong>.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2685\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/rename-wordpress-database-prefix-worpit.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2685   \" title=\"Worpit Feature: Rename WordPress Database Table Prefix\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/rename-wordpress-database-prefix-worpit-300x76.png\" alt=\"Worpit Feature: Rename WordPress Database Table Prefix\" width=\"300\" height=\"76\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Worpit Feature: Rename WordPress Database Table Prefix</p></div>\n<p>With Worpit &#8211; our dashboard for managing multiple WordPress sites &#8211; you can rename the prefix on 1 site, or on some/all your websites at once.</p>\n<p>This is the simplest way to do it, and you wont need any other plugins or other such addons.</p>\n<p>Not only that, you can take full advantage of all the other security features Worpit can offer your WordPress websites and you can <a title=\"Worpit App: Manage Multiple WordPress Websites\" href=\"http://worpitapp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">sign-up today for free</a>.</p>\n<h2>How to rename the WordPress Database Prefix &#8211; the <em>hard way</em></h2>\n<p>There are 5 steps to renaming the database table prefix:</p>\n<h4>1) Create a backup of the WordPress database and wp-config.php file</h4>\n<p>If you&#8217;re using <a title=\"WordPress Backup and Recovery\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress backup</a>, simply run a quick backup. After a few moments once it&#8217;s completed, continue on.</p>\n<h4>2) Edit your wp-config.php with the new prefix value</h4>\n<p>Open up your wp-config.php and change the value of the database prefix in the line that starts with <code>$table_prefix</code>.</p>\n<p>Remember to keep the quotes around the name of the prefix &#8211; very important.</p>\n<p>It could look something like:</p>\n<pre>$table_prefix = \'my_new_prefix_\';</pre>\n<h4>3) Change the names of the database tables</h4>\n<p>Open up an editor to your database, say in phpMyAdmin, browse to your database and click on SQL (see image below).</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2688\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/wordpress-database-prefix-run-sql-to-rename-tables.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2688  \" title=\"WordPress Database Prefix: Run SQL To Rename Tables\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/wordpress-database-prefix-run-sql-to-rename-tables-300x176.png\" alt=\"WordPress Database Prefix: Run SQL To Rename Tables\" width=\"300\" height=\"176\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Run SQL To Rename Tables</p></div>\n<p>To get you started, here is some SQL that you can use to rename your tables. In this case, we have assumed that your new prefix is: &#8216;my_new_prefix_&#8217;</p>\n<pre>RENAME table `wp_commentmeta` TO `my_new_prefix_commentmeta`;\nRENAME table `wp_comments` TO `my_new_prefix_comments`;\nRENAME table `wp_links` TO `my_new_prefix_links`;\nRENAME table `wp_options` TO `my_new_prefix_options`;\nRENAME table `wp_postmeta` TO `my_new_prefix_postmeta`;\nRENAME table `wp_posts` TO `my_new_prefix_posts`;\nRENAME table `wp_terms` TO `my_new_prefix_terms`;\nRENAME table `wp_term_relationships` TO `my_new_prefix_term_relationships`;\nRENAME table `wp_term_taxonomy` TO `my_new_prefix_term_taxonomy`;\nRENAME table `wp_usermeta` TO `my_new_prefix_usermeta`;\nRENAME table `wp_users` TO `my_new_prefix_users`;</pre>\n<h4>4) Update User Meta fields</h4>\n<p>This is often overlooked, but failing to update these will prevent you from logging in again.</p>\n<p>In the same window as before, use the command below to help you automatically find and replace all your necessary fields:</p>\n<pre><code>UPDATE `my_new_prefix_usermeta` SET `meta_key` = REPLACE( `meta_key`, \'wp_\', \'my_new_prefix_\' )</code></pre>\n<h4>5) Update options table data</h4>\n<p>Again, below, use the following command to update any options table data:</p>\n<pre><code>UPDATE `my_new_prefix_options` SET `option_name` = \'my_new_prefix_user_roles\' WHERE `option_name` = \'wp_user_roles\'</code></pre>\n<p>And you&#8217;re done.</p>\n<p>Again, if you&#8217;re not comfortable with manually editing your WordPress database table prefix, and other security settings, you can do them all in seconds using Worpit!</p>\n<h2>Get The Worpit Advantage Today</h2>\n<p>Worpit lets you manage your plugins, themes, and security (and much more) across all your WordPress website from one convenient, secure, dashboard.</p>\n<p>And it&#8217;s free to signup. No commitments, no credit cards. Just good WordPress management.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/jSGXYghBNCE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/changing-wordpress-database-table-prefix-security-obscurity/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/changing-wordpress-database-table-prefix-security-obscurity/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";